## Quality gates
- Keep CI fast, deterministic, and meaningful.
- Typical required checks include typecheck (`tsc --noEmit` or project equivalent), unit tests, lint (ESLint), and production build.
- Add dependency or security scanning (`pnpm audit`, Snyk, etc.) when the org standardizes on a tool.
- Do not weaken CI to bypass failing quality or security checks without an explicit justification.
- Prefer fixing flaky tests over retry-based masking.
- Keep local developer commands aligned with CI commands where practical.
